	abstract = {Purpose: In recent years, changes in global trade patterns, geopolitical instability and pandemics have greatly affected the security and reliability of global supply chains, highlighting the critical role and challenges of the logistics industry in the global economy. The logistics industry is large in scale and has the potential to provide support for future economic upgrading and transformation. However, China’s logistics industry still faces many contradictions, such as the imbalance between logistics supply and demand, under-utilization of resources and uncoordinated policy systems. These problems seriously constrain the further development of the logistics industry. Therefore, this paper chooses to take “Study on Heterogeneous Growth Patterns and Conversion Paths of China’s Logistics Industry” as its title, hoping to provide a little idea for policy making and subsequent research. The purpose of this study is to provide a useful reference for identifying heterogeneous growth patterns in China’s logistics industry and promoting coordinated regional development in the context of the dual circulation strategy. Design/methodology/approach: Firstly, the construction of the evaluation index system of the logistics industry and the use of the entropy method as an alternative to the subjective assignment method in order to provide a more objective and realistic evaluation and to reveal the development status of China’s provincial logistics industry through quantitative analyses. Secondly, a finite mixed model with accompanying variables is introduced. This method is able to classify the research object more objectively, thus avoiding the possible bias caused by subjective empirical grouping and uses the Poisson distribution to determine the affiliation probability of each path. Thirdly, the assumption of a constant growth pattern of an economy is abandoned, and a finite mixture model that reflects the path variation of the growth pattern of an economy is 