e and the promotion of coordinated regional development. Research limitations/implications: The limitations of this paper may exist in the following two aspects: Firstly, limitations in data acquisition: data in the logistics industry usually involves a large number of enterprises, but there may be differences in the openness and accuracy of the data in different regions and enterprises, and in particular the data of small and medium-sized enterprises may not be sufficiently transparent, which affects the comprehensiveness and accuracy of the study. Secondly, the impact of international factors: the increasing influence of global supply chain fluctuations and international logistics networks on China’s logistics industry, the study may be difficult to fully capture the long-term impact of international factors on the growth pattern of China’s logistics industry. Practical implications: This study can provide the government and relevant departments with appropriate data results. The Government can monitor and evaluate the data, which not only helps to identify the dynamics and changes in the logistics industry but also provides a timely basis for policy formulation. Originality/value: This study is an original work that aims to explore the heterogeneous growth model of China’s logistics industry and its conversion path. During the research process, I independently designed and implemented the research framework and methodology by relying on the relevant literature and data analysis tools. The data collection, model construction and conclusion derivation in the study are all based on my own analyses, without copying or applying existing research results and strive to provide new theoretical perspectives and practical basis for the development of the logistics industry. The opinions, conclusions and recommendations in this study are the result of my independent thinking. © 2025 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
